From a1b2c3d4e5f6a7b8c9d0e1f2a3b4c5d6e7f8a9b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Eric Lundby <Eric.Lundby@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 3 Mar 2026 10:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Remove spurious //tensorflow/core:framework dep from TFLite
 analyzer

The model_analyzer cc_library pulls in //tensorflow/core:framework which
transitively drags all of protos_all_cc into the TFLite shared library.
This causes duplicate protobuf descriptor registration at runtime
(tensor_shape.proto, etc.) when the profiler is loaded.

The dependency is unnecessary; model_analyzer only needs the headers
already provided by the other listed deps.

---
 tensorflow/lite/python/analyzer_wrapper/BUILD | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tensorflow/lite/python/analyzer_wrapper/BUILD b/tensorflow/lite/python/analyzer_wrapper/BUILD
index f40c8b28c7b..6560db7cd90 100644
--- a/tensorflow/lite/python/analyzer_wrapper/BUILD
+++ b/tensorflow/lite/python/analyzer_wrapper/BUILD
@@ -34,7 +34,6 @@ cc_library(
     visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
     deps = [
         "//tensorflow/compiler/mlir/lite/schema:schema_utils",
-        "//tensorflow/core:framework",
         "//tensorflow/core/public:release_version",
         "//tensorflow/lite:version",
         "//tensorflow/lite/core:model_builder",
